Case 003 – Browser History & Download Activity Investigation
Executive Summary

This investigation examined browser artifacts and downloaded files on a Windows 11 system to determine whether a user accessed websites and downloaded files using Google Chrome.

The investigation focused on browser history, download records, file metadata, and cryptographic hashes. Evidence confirmed that multiple files were downloaded through Chrome and remained present on the system at the time of analysis.

Scenario

A user is suspected of downloading files from the internet. The objective is to determine:

Which browser was used
What files were downloaded
When the downloads occurred
Whether the files still exist
Whether file integrity can be verified
Tools Used
Tool	Purpose
Google Chrome	Source of browser artifacts
File Explorer	Evidence collection
PowerShell	Metadata and hash analysis
Windows 11	Investigation platform
Evidence Collection
Browser Artifact Location
%LOCALAPPDATA%\Google\Chrome\User Data\Default\History

The Chrome History database was identified and preserved as evidence.

Evidence Files
Evidence Item	Description
History	Chrome browsing and download database
Downloads Folder	Downloaded files
InvestigationNotes.txt	Test file created during investigation
PowerShell Output	Metadata collection
SHA256 Hashes	File integrity verification
Investigation Steps
1. Browser Activity

Google Chrome was identified as the browser used during the investigation.

The Chrome History database was located within the user's profile directory.

Screenshot:

screenshots/chrome-history-file.png
2. Download History Review

Chrome download history was examined to identify downloaded files.

Evidence showed:

PDF file download
ZIP file download

Screenshot:

screenshots/browser-downloads.png
3. Downloads Folder Analysis

The Downloads directory was examined to verify that the downloaded files remained present on the system.

Observed files:

File Name	Type
G162691946_78d2eb5c69934a7ca6e8d9ba28f8724c.pdf	PDF
cmeofalltrades power-bi-portfolio main Project-02-Device-Compliance.zip	ZIP
InvestigationNotes.txt	Text File

Screenshot:

screenshots/downloads-folder.png
4. Metadata Analysis

PowerShell was used to review file creation and modification timestamps.

Get-ChildItem "$env:USERPROFILE\Downloads" |
Sort-Object CreationTime -Descending |
Select-Object -First 10 Name, CreationTime, LastWriteTime

Results:

File	Creation Time
ZIP File	06/24/2026 09:44:26
PDF File	06/24/2026 09:49:34
InvestigationNotes.txt	06/24/2026 09:50:53

Screenshot:

screenshots/download-metadata.png
5. Hash Verification

SHA256 hashes were generated to establish file integrity.

PDF File
